        <Parent_String>Agnatha (class) [300249651], Vertebrata (subphylum) [300265720], Chordata (phylum) [300266513], Animalia (kingdom) [300249395], Eukaryota (domain) [300265677], living organisms (entities) [300390503], Living Organisms (hierarchy name) [300265673], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Order containing 22 species of primitive, eel-like, jawless vertebrates that are scaleless, have a funnel-like toothed sucking mouth, no paired fins, large eyes, one nostril on the top of the head, and seven gills on each side. The animals begin life as burrowing freshwater larvae (ammocoetes), which are toothless, have rudimentary eyes, and feed on microorganisms; they transform into adults via a metamorphosis that is as radical as that seen in amphibians.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>含二十二種類似鰻魚的原始脊椎動物；無頜無鱗，擁有狀似漏斗且有牙的吸嘴，無對鰭，眼大，頭頂有一個鼻孔，每側具七個鰓。七鰓鰻目在幼體時期(幼鰓鰻)藏於洞穴中，無牙，眼睛未發展完全，以微生物為食。歷經變態演變為成體，與兩棲類相似，變態前後有明顯的不同。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
